<h1 id="myHeader">CSS Manipulation </h1>

<p id="one">
The meanest dog you'll ever meet<br>
He ain't the hound dog in the street<br>
He bares some teeth and tears some skin but brother
That's the worst of him<br>
The dog you really got to dread is the one that howls inside your head<br>
It's him whose howling drives men mad<br>
And a mind to its undoing<br><br>

You got a lonesome road to walk<br>
And it ain't along the railroad tracks<br>
It ain't along the blacktop tar you've walked a hundred times before<br>
I'll tell you where the real road lies<br>
Between your ears, behind your eyes<br>
That is the path to paradise<br>
And likewise the road to ruin<br><br>
</p>

<label for="border">Border:</label><br>
<label for="border">Red Value (00-FF):</label><br>
<input type="text" id="boardred" name="boardred"><br><br>
<label for="border">Blue Value (00-FF):</label><br>
<input type="text" id="boardblue" name="boardblue"><br><br>
<label for="border">Green Value (00-FF):</label><br>
<input type="text" id="boardgreen" name="boardgreen"><br><br>
<label for="border">Width (int):</label><br>
<input type="text" id="boardwidth" name="boardwidth"><br><br><br><br>

<label for="background">Background:</label><br>
<label for="background">Red Value (00-FF):</label><br>
<input type="text" id="backred" name="backred"><br><br>
<label for="background">Blue Value (00-FF):</label><br>
<input type="text" id="backblue" name="backblue"><br><br>
<label for="background">Green Value (00-FF):</label><br>
<input type="text" id="backgreen" name="backgreen"><br><br>

<button onclick="update()">Update</button>

<script>



function update() {
document.getElementById("one").style.borderColor =("#"+String(document.getElementById("boardred").value)+String(document.getElementById("boardblue").value)+String(document.getElementById("boardgreen").value)); 

document.getElementById("one").style.borderWidth = String(document.getElementById("boardwidth").value)+"px";

document.getElementById("one").style.backgroundColor =("#"+String(document.getElementById("backred").value)+String(document.getElementById("backblue").value)+String(document.getElementById("backgreen").value)); 
}

</script>

